Description:
Your Own Backyard
This established townhouse in a small block of 12 is at the end of the cul-de-sac and the back of the complex for your quiet enjoyment. The newly renovated kitchen has timber flooring extending out through to the living/ dining area. The backyard is a unique draw card, perfect for pets and entertaining friends. The car park is undercover and secure with enough room to fit a storage unit at the end. The building features; bike racks, 6 off-street visitor car parks and a pedestrian R.O.W to Walsh Street which is just moments away from the botanical gardens.

Description:
LOCATION, LOCATION, LOCATION!
Recently renovated, this bright and airy apartment welcomes plenty of natural light, and is hands down, the best on the block!
Featuring a new kitchen, flooring, and airconditioning, this well-maintained block comes with landscaped gardens and an outdoor swimming pool.
Simplistic in style with a cool and leafy outlook from the living area, your 1-bedroom apartment has everything you need. Including a laundry on each level, and secure undercover parking, youre also just a couple of steps from an almost-private café on Luxton.
Situated in a perfect position, walk to Chapel Street, Hawksburn Village and Toorak Road, where youre surrounded by retail shops, eateries and lively bars. Just a couple minutes walk to Hawksburn Station, trams and buses, youre also just 35 minutes away from Melbourne Airport.
Ideal for young couples, business professionals, and investors alike, this is a fantastic opportunity waiting to be snapped up.
Call Lori Ille on 0490815632 and kickstart the new year in your very own apartment in one of Melbournes best locations.
Features:
1-Bedroom Apartment
Built-in-Robe
Newly Renovated Kitchen & Flooring
Airconditioning
Secure undercover parking
Laundry on each level
In-ground outdoor swimming pool
Well-maintained and landscaped gardens
Fantastic location in the heart of cafes, transport and eateries.

Description:
Sunlight Delight On The Edge Of The Botanic Gardens
In a location synonymous with high fashion, great food and the good life, this first-floor north-facing apartment is perfectly positioned to enjoy the South Yarra lifestyle in the prestigious Botanical Gardens Precinct. Streaming northern sunshine floods into the living room with a balcony that enjoys leafy views to frame the street-scape. The floorplan is fantastic, with a central hallway that leads off to the separate rooms. The separate kitchen highlights the generous interior proportions, including laundry facilities and can be improved in the future. Large windows dominate the north facing bedroom, which enjoys a luxurious walk-in robe and located across the hall you will find a light and bright bathroom with shower over bath. With great potential to improve in the future and off-street parking on title this apartment is not to be missed. Larger than most one bedroom apartments, this is an ideal lock-up and leave scenario for busy professionals, retirees in search of a city base or first time buyers looking for an exclusive address in the heart of South Yarra lifestyle precinct close to Toorak Rd shops South Yarra Station, buses, trams, excellent shopping and walking distance to Fawkner Park and MCG sports precinct.

Sublime Split-level Style, South Yarra Hill Exclusivity
This sublime two-story two-bedroom apartment with a basement car space resides in a premier South Yarra Hill location within a secure complex, which has been cleverly fashioned around a central internal courtyard. Superb attention to detail is matched with exquisite finishes creating memorable surroundings for property debutants, canny investors and lifestyle seekers. The property features a generously light-filled living and dining domain along with a stone finished kitchen with quality stainless steel appliances. Upstairs, two double bedrooms with mirrored robes enjoy a stylish marble finished bathroom. Completed with central heating, marble finished powder room on lower level with expansive storage under the staircase, new carpet, European laundry and lift access, this stylish home delivers low-maintenance living at its fashionable best. From this amazing location you can stroll to Toorak Roads boutique shops and restaurants and vibrant Chapel Street, South Yarra station, the No.8 tram on Toorak Road, the Royal Botantic Gardens and Fawkner Park. Cycling enthusiasts will love the access to the CBD and Melbournes sporting precinct along the nearby Yarra rivers beautiful bike and walking paths.

Description:
Style and Convenience In the Heart of South Yarra
Located in the boutique SEE Apartment development, this stylish property offers the best of low maintenance inner urban living in the heart of South Yarra, just moments from both trams and trains, along with an array of luxury boutiques, shops, cafes, restaurants and bars.
A contemporary neutral interior and space optimising design characterise this 13th floor apartment, comprising of a carpeted bedroom containing generous BIR’s, neat white tiled bathroom and study/second bedroom. Beside a discreetly located euro laundry, the streamlined galley kitchen features integrated dishwasher, gas cooktop, wall oven, stone benches and capacious storage cabinetry; servicing a light filled and air-conditioned open-plan living room accessing a covered angled balcony with room to entertain. Residents enjoy exclusive access to a funky roof top terrace with BBQ, gas fire and panoramic views across Melbourne. An area popular with renters makes this a savvy investment option, while the area’s brilliant infrastructure and amenities create the ideal first home opportunity.

Description:
Peerless Style and Luxury in the Domain Precinct - Construction Complete
Set in a prominent position in South Yarra's sought-after Domain precinct, Pask Group presents the Millswyn.
A collection of Rob Mills designed residences, crowned by the gardens of Paul Bangay. Inspired by its locale, nestled between the Botanical Gardens and Fawkner Park, Millswyn Residences embody exceptional architecture, landscaping and luxury finishes, all which unite to create an unparalleled and sophisticated lifestyle.
Residence seven enjoys light filled elevated first floor living, impressively proportioned dimensions, showcasing the finest in contemporary elegance and luxury. Three metre plus ceilings and full height doors and windows accentuate the sense of space and light throughout. Wide Oak floors flow through an entrance gallery to an expansive living and dining room. The sublime kitchen is appointed with premium appliances and marble benches. The living space opens to a private landscaped Paul Bangay garden terrace, ideal for al fresco dining and entertaining. Main bedroom with opulent marble en-suite and walk in robe sets a benchmark for luxury that is met by two additional double bedrooms with built in robes and marble en-suites. Car accommodation has been well considered with enclosed double garage plus storage room.
A commitment to craftsmanship without compromise; from the monumental isernia limestone façade, exquisite finishes including Italian Calcutta marble and Royal Oak floors, all elements have been carefully considered to bring together a unique offering in arguably Melbourne's most prestigious and sought-after location.

Description:
Luxury, Low-Maintenance Living in Privileged Position - PRICED TO SELL
Led by light-filled luxury, balanced design and detailed comfort, this impeccably stylish 3 bedroom home dazzles and delights over two lavish levels in a serene setting, moments from the vitality of Toorak Road and Chapel Street.
Discover a glistening, granite-topped kitchen boasting Smeg appliances and a handy breakfast bar for relaxed meal times. Free-flowing throughout, a large, light and bright open-plan living and dining area is framed by seamlessly integrated cabinetry and joinery.
The efficient and effective use of space inside and out is a triumph of thoughtful planning. Enjoy the day-to-day flexibility of outdoor entertaining with French doors spilling outside to a walled, sandstone courtyard. Perfectly private and facing north, this elegant, hedge-framed space is sure to be a hit this coming summer.
All bedrooms are zoned upstairs for privacy, serviced by a pair of sparkling bathrooms. Comprehensive features include sleek herringbone parquetry flooring, security door and intercom entry, heating/cooling and stylish plantation shutters. A remote-controlled garage boasting internal access completes a home entirely in tune with modern demands.
Take full advantage of a premier South Yarra address within walking distance of South Yarra station, Fawkner Park and the suburb’s celebrated restaurants and cafes. Offering timeless, easy-care elegance, this home is ideal for those with high expectations, busy lifestyles and lock-and-leave ambitions. Inspect with confidence today!
* 3 large bedrooms, main with sparkling ensuite
* Elegant open-plan living and dining with gas open fireplace
* Stylish Smeg kitchen with granite benchtops, tiled splashback and breakfast bar
* Skylit family bathroom featuring a sumptuous bath
* Concealed laundry
* Handy ground-floor powder room
* Storage under stairs
* Sun-drenched, north-facing courtyard
* Remote-controlled garage featuring internal access
* Plantation shutters upstairs
* Secure gated intercom entry
* Timed watering system servicing low-maintenance garden
* Alarm system
* Extensive heating and cooling
* Moments from cafes, restaurants, nightlife, transport, shopping, schools and parkland
